Usage: analyze_esd_voltage [-help] -current_distribution_layer <string>
                           [-detailed_report <string>]
                           -driver_receiver_file <string>
                           -esd_pin_location_file <string>
                           [-maximum_violations <integer>] -net <string>
                           [-report <string>] [-threshold <float>]
                           -total_current <string>

-help                                    # Prints out the command usage
-current_distribution_layer <string>     # current distribution layer
                                         # (string, required)
-detailed_report <string>                # output detail report file name
                                         # (string, optional)
-driver_receiver_file <string>           # <driver/receiver file of the net>
                                         # (string, required)
-esd_pin_location_file <string>          # <esd pin location file>
                                         # (string, required)
-maximum_violations <integer>            # number of max worst violations to be
                                         # reported (int, optional)
-net <string>                            # <name of the net to be analyzed>
                                         # (string, required)
-report <string>                         # output report file name
                                         # (string, optional)
-threshold <float>                       # minimum threshold driver/receiver
                                         # voltage in volt for report filtering
                                         # (float, optional)
-total_current <string>                  # total esd current to be distributed
                                         # (string, required)